                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Portugal/1537: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-09T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 9, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1680. Reference your 1755, June 7, and London’s 4569, June 7. Department and FEA
                    entirely agree with proposal to cancel surcharges. Sent to Lisbon, repeated to
                    London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
